Merge pull request #36 from FlashSystems/master

Config merging is not working because the default values are indistigâ€¦

Merge pull request #37 from FlashSystems/Satisfy-Any

Fix for: "Satisfy Any" to allow unauthenticated access from specific IPs not working.

The apache directive "Satisfy: Any" will not work. The hook ap_hook_check_authn must be used instead of ap_hook_check_access to prevent superfluous password requests. Details can be found in this bug https://github.com/Jasig/mod_auth_cas/issues/93 .

Config merging is not working because the default values are indistiguishable from user set values. Changed the default values so config merging works as expected. The problem can be reproduced by changing the port. Config merging merges the default port over the user set global value.

Merge pull request #34 from frenche/send_auth_header

Always add WWW-Authenticate header when auth fails

Always add WWW-Authenticate header when auth fails

This is required so the user agent can determine what auth
method is supported.

Quote from RFC 2617:
If the origin server does not wish to accept the credentials sent
with a request, it SHOULD return a 401 (Unauthorized) response. The
response MUST include a WWW-Authenticate header field containing at
least one (possibly new) challenge applicable to the requested
resource.
